00:02:33.070 --> 00:02:37.300 align:middle line:10%
And if we're having fun and we
feel connected to other people

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:41.050 align:middle line:10%
and feel safe and cared
for, we learn more rapidly

00:02:41.050 --> 00:02:44.000 align:middle line:10%
and retain the
information longer.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.870 align:middle line:84%
>> So a child, or even
a student in college,

00:02:46.870 --> 00:02:48.550 align:middle line:84%
or someone that's
gone back to college,

00:02:48.550 --> 00:02:50.050 align:middle line:84%
anything that we're
trying to learn,

00:02:50.050 --> 00:02:54.640 align:middle line:84%
if we can in some way make it
appeal to our, where we are

00:02:54.640 --> 00:02:56.230 align:middle line:90%
emotionally, it will help?

00:02:56.230 --> 00:02:57.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:02:57.290 --> 00:02:58.090 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:02:58.090 --> 00:03:02.320 align:middle line:84%
And recognizing the place
and the value of each emotion

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:03.730 align:middle line:90%
is essential.

00:03:03.730 --> 00:03:05.650 align:middle line:90%
Fear and anger have their place.

00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:08.180 align:middle line:90%
And yet, they inhibit learning.

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:10.663 align:middle line:84%
>> So if I am trying to learn
something and I'm fearful

00:03:10.663 --> 00:03:13.330 align:middle line:84%
of that I'm not going to be able
to learn it or there's anything

00:03:13.330 --> 00:03:16.990 align:middle line:84%
in my personal life that's
going on, or if the instructor

00:03:16.990 --> 00:03:19.780 align:middle line:84%
