00:11:46.920 --> 00:11:48.600 align:middle line:84%
And welcome back to
"A World of Wisdom."

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:51.330 align:middle line:10%
I'm Carolyn Craft, and I'm
speaking with Dr. Bill DeFoore.

00:11:51.330 --> 00:11:53.940 align:middle line:10%
And we are talking about
emotional intelligence.

00:11:53.940 --> 00:11:56.550 align:middle line:10%
And specifically,
we were speaking

00:11:56.550 --> 00:11:59.460 align:middle line:10%
earlier about emotional
intelligence in the workplace.

00:11:59.460 --> 00:12:04.410 align:middle line:84%
Something you say, business
is always personal.

00:12:04.410 --> 00:12:08.010 align:middle line:84%
Explain how it's
always personal for us.

00:12:08.010 --> 00:12:10.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, in a kind of
a philosophical sense,

00:12:10.870 --> 00:12:15.590 align:middle line:10%
we could say that there aren't
any people on this planet who

00:12:15.590 --> 00:12:18.840 align:middle line:10%
are not engaged in
some kind of business.

00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:23.700 align:middle line:10%
And so to that extent,
everyone is a business person.

00:12:23.700 --> 00:12:26.550 align:middle line:10%
From the person on the
street corner with a tin can

00:12:26.550 --> 00:12:28.390 align:middle line:10%
and maybe a little
homemade instrument,

00:12:28.390 --> 00:12:32.880 align:middle line:10%
they're trying to get
people to contribute with,

00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:35.940 align:middle line:10%
to the person who's
literally buying and selling

00:12:35.940 --> 00:12:37.710 align:middle line:10%
money on Wall Street.

00:12:37.710 --> 00:12:40.410 align:middle line:84%
And on the full range,
that's all exchange

00:12:40.410 --> 00:12:42.970 align:middle line:90%
of goods and services.

00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:46.830 align:middle line:84%
And in another
sense, our economy,

00:12:46.830 --> 00:12:50.970 align:middle line:84%
our global economy
affects everyone.

00:12:50.970 --> 00:12:54.030 align:middle line:84%
So what happens in
the business world,

00:12:54.030 --> 00:12:56.400 align:middle line:84%
decisions made by
corporate leaders,

00:12:56.400 --> 00:13:01.410 align:middle line:84%
by government leaders
regarding economic values,

00:13:01.410 --> 00:13:03.190 align:middle line:90%
affects everyone.

00:13:03.190 --> 00:13:05.970 align:middle line:84%
It affects the quality
of goods and services

00:13:05.970 --> 00:13:07.570 align:middle line:90%
that are available to us.

00:13:07.570 --> 00:13:11.740 align:middle line:84%
It affects the availability
of those goods and services.

00:13:11.740 --> 00:13:15.630 align:middle line:84%
So our economy is
a living, breathing

00:13:15.630 --> 00:13:18.880 align:middle line:90%
aspect of our consciousness.

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:21.250 align:middle line:90%
And we are all part of that.

00:13:21.250 --> 00:13:24.360 align:middle line:84%
So to that extent,
business is personal.

00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:28.890 align:middle line:84%
If something happens in Japan
with their economy, we feel it.

00:13:28.890 --> 00:13:34.150 align:middle line:10%
And we recently had a major
crisis in the Eastern economy

00:13:34.150 --> 00:13:38.550 align:middle line:10%
which had a great impact
on our stock prices.

00:13:38.550 --> 00:13:44.310 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems like that you talk
about the shadow side of what

00:13:44.310 --> 00:13:47.730 align:middle line:84%
we bring to business,
and business shadow side.

00:13:47.730 --> 00:13:51.000 align:middle line:84%
It seems like in addressing
the emotional intelligence,

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:54.540 align:middle line:84%
we're perhaps putting light
on what is already personal

00:13:54.540 --> 00:13:56.250 align:middle line:84%
anyway and happening
there anyway?

00:13:56.250 --> 00:13:57.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:57.990 --> 00:14:03.810 align:middle line:10%
It's rather than running from
that downturn in our profits

00:14:03.810 --> 00:14:09.270 align:middle line:10%
or pretending that the conflicts
and the vendettas and the games

00:14:09.270 --> 00:14:11.860 align:middle line:10%
and the backstabbing
at work are not there,

00:14:11.860 --> 00:14:13.980 align:middle line:10%
we turn and look
directly at them.

00:14:13.980 --> 00:14:17.070 align:middle line:84%
And we look not at them to
fix them or change them,

00:14:17.070 --> 00:14:19.300 align:middle line:90%
but to find the value.

00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:21.780 align:middle line:84%
What is the learning
that we can gain

00:14:21.780 --> 00:14:25.830 align:middle line:84%
from examining exactly what's
going on in this perhaps

00:14:25.830 --> 00:14:28.650 align:middle line:84%
long-term vendetta,
which can be extremely

00:14:28.650 --> 00:14:30.960 align:middle line:84%
costly in the
business relationship.

00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:32.490 align:middle line:90%
Or in a family.

00:14:32.490 --> 00:14:36.060 align:middle line:84%
If two people in a family
are not getting along,

00:14:36.060 --> 00:14:38.070 align:middle line:84%
it affects everyone
else in the family

00:14:38.070 --> 00:14:41.790 align:middle line:84%
and it has a tremendous
emotional drain on everyone.

00:14:41.790 --> 00:14:44.550 align:middle line:84%
What can be gained by
looking specifically at that

00:14:44.550 --> 00:14:49.080 align:middle line:84%
and using some very clear and
practical tools for opening it

00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:51.420 align:middle line:90%
up to meaningful communication?

00:14:51.420 --> 00:14:53.190 align:middle line:84%
>> You do workshops
all over the world.

00:14:53.190 --> 00:14:57.180 align:middle line:84%
And you work with
businesses, in particular two

00:14:57.180 --> 00:14:59.670 align:middle line:90%
that are opening up to this.

00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:02.940 align:middle line:84%
They do need a facilitator
in the beginning,

00:15:02.940 --> 00:15:05.280 align:middle line:84%
I would think, to
understand this.

00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:06.450 align:middle line:90%
Then what do they do?

00:15:06.450 --> 00:15:08.460 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what happens--

00:15:08.460 --> 00:15:10.650 align:middle line:84%
again, going back to
that board meeting.

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:13.510 align:middle line:84%
We all come in around
the table there.

00:15:13.510 --> 00:15:17.730 align:middle line:84%
And you've been there and shared
with us some ways to sit there

00:15:17.730 --> 00:15:20.700 align:middle line:84%
and actually share
what's going on with us.

00:15:20.700 --> 00:15:22.590 align:middle line:90%
And then you're gone.

00:15:22.590 --> 00:15:25.560 align:middle line:84%
What helps us make
that transition

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:27.600 align:middle line:84%
and know that that's
a real good thing

00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:31.320 align:middle line:84%
to be doing with one another,
to really understand and manage

00:15:31.320 --> 00:15:33.600 align:middle line:90%
our emotional intelligence?

00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:37.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Organizations that
apply these principles

00:15:37.080 --> 00:15:42.620 align:middle line:84%
on a consistent basis
increase their level of trust.

00:15:42.620 --> 00:15:44.790 align:middle line:84%
And because their level
of trust is increased,

00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:49.740 align:middle line:84%
they're more honest and
more current and more open.

00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:54.510 align:middle line:84%
And then the empowerment of
individuals and work teams

00:15:54.510 --> 00:15:56.150 align:middle line:90%
automatically results.

00:15:56.150 --> 00:15:59.722 align:middle line:84%
And business leaders will
say, you take care of that.

00:15:59.722 --> 00:16:00.930 align:middle line:90%
Let me know how you're doing.

00:16:00.930 --> 00:16:01.860 align:middle line:90%
Ask my advice.

00:16:01.860 --> 00:16:02.760 align:middle line:90%
But it's your deal.

00:16:02.760 --> 00:16:04.980 align:middle line:84%
I trust you to
take care of that.

00:16:04.980 --> 00:16:07.170 align:middle line:84%
One organization,
a power company

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:09.840 align:middle line:84%
that has plants
all over the world,

00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:15.930 align:middle line:84%
has someone who is a head of
maintenance doing fundraising,

00:16:15.930 --> 00:16:17.155 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:16:17.155 --> 00:16:18.030 align:middle line:90%
And that's wonderful.

00:16:18.030 --> 00:16:21.360 align:middle line:84%
You know, when the rigid job
description doesn't confine

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:25.800 align:middle line:84%
someone and people are empowered
to be innovative and creative

00:16:25.800 --> 00:16:33.030 align:middle line:84%
and use untapped resources,
it's wonderful and amazing what

00:16:33.030 --> 00:16:34.850 align:middle line:90%
can happen in an organization.

00:16:34.850 --> 00:16:37.680 align:middle line:84%
>> There is an automatic
care that's understood, too.

00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:41.040 align:middle line:84%
And I want to know what
is going on with you.

00:16:41.040 --> 00:16:44.520 align:middle line:84%
Not to be your therapist, but
to know that that part of you

00:16:44.520 --> 00:16:46.990 align:middle line:84%
that you bring that is
in sorrow or whatever

00:16:46.990 --> 00:16:47.950 align:middle line:90%
is an important part.

00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:53.940 align:middle line:84%
It seems that it would help
just overall communication.

00:16:53.940 --> 00:16:57.040 align:middle line:84%
And I think you talk
also about the retention

00:16:57.040 --> 00:16:59.540 align:middle line:90%
level with employees.

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:01.210 align:middle line:90%
How does it help that?

00:17:01.210 --> 00:17:07.240 align:middle line:84%
>> If, or when, individuals feel
cared for in an organization,

00:17:07.240 --> 00:17:08.890 align:middle line:90%
they're more likely to stay.

00:17:08.890 --> 00:17:10.990 align:middle line:10%
The workplace surveys
that have been conducted

00:17:10.990 --> 00:17:13.900 align:middle line:10%
indicate that pay is
third or fourth down

00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:15.700 align:middle line:10%
in terms of priority.

00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:19.510 align:middle line:84%
Feeling connected and a
part of the organization

00:17:19.510 --> 00:17:21.490 align:middle line:90%
is one of the first.

00:17:21.490 --> 00:17:25.869 align:middle line:10%
Another one of the top ones is
feeling an alliance of vision

00:17:25.869 --> 00:17:28.150 align:middle line:10%
and purpose and
feeling that they

00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:31.810 align:middle line:10%
are making a contribution
that is meaningful to them

00:17:31.810 --> 00:17:33.490 align:middle line:10%
through their work.

00:17:33.490 --> 00:17:37.390 align:middle line:10%
>> And I'm hearing, too,
that we can learn this.

00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:39.950 align:middle line:10%
This is something
that can be learned.

00:17:39.950 --> 00:17:42.850 align:middle line:10%
It's not something that someone
has and someone doesn't.

00:17:42.850 --> 00:17:44.800 align:middle line:84%
>> It's how we're
designed, Carolyn.

00:17:44.800 --> 00:17:48.100 align:middle line:84%
We were designed to be
joyful, exuberant, creative,

00:17:48.100 --> 00:17:50.620 align:middle line:90%
magnificent beings.

00:17:50.620 --> 00:17:57.100 align:middle line:84%
And unexpressed fear, pain, and
anger block that brilliance.

00:17:57.100 --> 00:17:59.530 align:middle line:84%
So we don't talk
about fear and pain

00:17:59.530 --> 00:18:02.470 align:middle line:84%
and anger because
it's fun, simply

00:18:02.470 --> 00:18:05.470 align:middle line:84%
because it is
effective for untapping

00:18:05.470 --> 00:18:09.270 align:middle line:84%
the brilliance, the light
that is behind all of that.

00:18:09.270 --> 00:18:12.190 align:middle line:84%
>> You say there are
three areas, at least,

00:18:12.190 --> 00:18:13.660 align:middle line:90%
business and personal.

00:18:13.660 --> 00:18:15.730 align:middle line:84%
And there's also
a spiritual level

00:18:15.730 --> 00:18:19.060 align:middle line:84%
that is helped if
we can understand

00:18:19.060 --> 00:18:21.610 align:middle line:90%
our emotional intelligence.

00:18:21.610 --> 00:18:24.190 align:middle line:10%
>> You know, it's found that
people who have a spiritual

00:18:24.190 --> 00:18:27.370 align:middle line:10%
connection of some kind are
healthier physically and live

00:18:27.370 --> 00:18:28.670 align:middle line:10%
longer.

00:18:28.670 --> 00:18:31.960 align:middle line:10%
It's often also found
that business leaders who

00:18:31.960 --> 00:18:34.330 align:middle line:10%
have some kind of
spiritual focus

00:18:34.330 --> 00:18:37.750 align:middle line:10%
tend to be able to integrate
some elements of that

00:18:37.750 --> 00:18:39.670 align:middle line:10%
into their work.

00:18:39.670 --> 00:18:44.390 align:middle line:84%
So for many people, a spiritual
focus is extremely important.

00:18:44.390 --> 00:18:48.190 align:middle line:84%
One of the elements
of that is faith.

00:18:48.190 --> 00:18:51.100 align:middle line:84%
And faith and optimism
have been found

00:18:51.100 --> 00:18:55.810 align:middle line:84%
to consistently correlate
with health and resiliency

00:18:55.810 --> 00:18:59.170 align:middle line:90%
regarding illness.

00:18:59.170 --> 00:19:03.130 align:middle line:84%
So spirituality has some very
practical health-related value

00:19:03.130 --> 00:19:04.240 align:middle line:90%
and benefit.

00:19:04.240 --> 00:19:07.840 align:middle line:84%
The way it relates to emotional
intelligence is to the extent

00:19:07.840 --> 00:19:11.290 align:middle line:84%
that we are captivated
by and controlled

00:19:11.290 --> 00:19:15.940 align:middle line:84%
by our fear, or our
anger, or our vendetta,

00:19:15.940 --> 00:19:18.580 align:middle line:84%
or controlled and held
back by sorrow, or perhaps

00:19:18.580 --> 00:19:22.690 align:middle line:84%
related depression, our
spirituality is blocked.

00:19:22.690 --> 00:19:27.070 align:middle line:84%
Spirituality aligns
itself with the emotions

00:19:27.070 --> 00:19:30.460 align:middle line:90%
of joy, love, and exuberance.

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:34.240 align:middle line:10%
And that is an
infinite wellspring

00:19:34.240 --> 00:19:35.990 align:middle line:10%
inside every one of us.

00:19:35.990 --> 00:19:39.150 align:middle line:84%
>> That's what keeps us
young, and getting younger.

00:19:39.150 --> 00:19:43.120 align:middle line:84%
What does an organization
look like that is managing

00:19:43.120 --> 00:19:46.270 align:middle line:90%
the emotional intelligence?

00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:47.180 align:middle line:90%
Themselves and other.

00:19:47.180 --> 00:19:47.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:50.500 align:middle line:90%
The people love their work.

00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:52.780 align:middle line:90%
They're excited, energetic.

00:19:52.780 --> 00:19:54.230 align:middle line:90%
They're real.

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:57.520 align:middle line:10%
They're talking with each
other about their lives.

00:19:57.520 --> 00:19:58.720 align:middle line:90%
They're fully present.

00:19:58.720 --> 00:20:01.150 align:middle line:84%
They didn't leave their
heart or their body

00:20:01.150 --> 00:20:05.090 align:middle line:84%
or their other personal
issues at the door.

00:20:05.090 --> 00:20:08.240 align:middle line:84%
They brought their whole
selves into the workplace.

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:11.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So they're not cut off
from, this is my business life

00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:12.370 align:middle line:90%
and this is my personal life.

00:20:12.370 --> 00:20:13.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Not at all.

00:20:13.640 --> 00:20:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And brilliantly creative, trying
things no one else has tried

00:20:19.420 --> 00:20:24.220 align:middle line:84%
and succeeding, and
literally breaking records

00:20:24.220 --> 00:20:28.880 align:middle line:84%
with profitability and growth
and sustainable, grounded

00:20:28.880 --> 00:20:29.680 align:middle line:90%
growth.

00:20:29.680 --> 00:20:33.595 align:middle line:84%
Because often growth is like the
first indication of a decline.

00:20:33.595 --> 00:20:36.280 align:middle line:90%


00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:38.440 align:middle line:84%
>> If we know the
benefits of this,

00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:42.100 align:middle line:84%
then what keeps us from
exploring it and allowing

00:20:42.100 --> 00:20:45.850 align:middle line:84%
someone to be fully who they
are in the business environment

00:20:45.850 --> 00:20:48.100 align:middle line:90%
or in our personal environment?

00:20:48.100 --> 00:20:49.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Two things.

00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:52.690 align:middle line:84%
One is the presence
and the prevalence

00:20:52.690 --> 00:20:54.850 align:middle line:90%
of fear in human consciousness.

00:20:54.850 --> 00:20:56.080 align:middle line:90%
It's huge.

00:20:56.080 --> 00:21:01.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's fed by much of what is
in the media and much of what

00:21:01.330 --> 00:21:04.900 align:middle line:84%
is just in human consciousness
and in conversation.

00:21:04.900 --> 00:21:07.750 align:middle line:84%
The game of ain't
it awful and talking

00:21:07.750 --> 00:21:10.750 align:middle line:84%
about how bad things are
is a very popular game

00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:12.932 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of people
play a lot of the time.

00:21:12.932 --> 00:21:15.140 align:middle line:84%
>> It's like playing the
same CD over and over again.

00:21:15.140 --> 00:21:15.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:17.320 align:middle line:84%
Unconsciously,
we're feeding fear.

00:21:17.320 --> 00:21:18.200 align:middle line:90%
That's one thing.

00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:19.990 align:middle line:90%
And the other is education.

00:21:19.990 --> 00:21:24.430 align:middle line:10%
We have not been educated,
in any formal sense,

00:21:24.430 --> 00:21:26.800 align:middle line:10%
about our emotions.

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:28.900 align:middle line:84%
We've always had
them, but we've never

00:21:28.900 --> 00:21:33.110 align:middle line:84%
made a specific attempt to
become intelligent about them.

00:21:33.110 --> 00:21:34.690 align:middle line:90%
>> What do you recommend to--

00:21:34.690 --> 00:21:36.820 align:middle line:90%
in our final moments here--

00:21:36.820 --> 00:21:41.710 align:middle line:84%
to someone who wants to
explore more about this?

00:21:41.710 --> 00:21:44.650 align:middle line:84%
Other than we're going
to be having your books

00:21:44.650 --> 00:21:45.960 align:middle line:90%
on during the breaks.

00:21:45.960 --> 00:21:49.080 align:middle line:90%
But what else could they do?

00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:50.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Tell your story.

00:21:50.730 --> 00:21:54.000 align:middle line:84%
I would recommend to the viewers
that they tell their story

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.920 align:middle line:90%
to people who matter to them.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:59.550 align:middle line:10%
Tell about the best and the
worst of times, the memories

00:21:59.550 --> 00:22:01.530 align:middle line:10%
that have never gone away.

00:22:01.530 --> 00:22:04.140 align:middle line:10%
And ask the people
that they love

00:22:04.140 --> 00:22:07.573 align:middle line:10%
for their stories, the best
and the worst of those stories.

00:22:07.573 --> 00:22:09.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Bill DeFoore, thank you so
much for being with us on "A

00:22:09.990 --> 00:22:13.290 align:middle line:84%
World of Wisdom" and in
opening our heart and sharing

